The Telegraph - Calcutta
 AIFF task force for 2010 Cup 
 BY A STAFF REPORTER Calcutta: The AIFF has decided to take some steps to ensure Indias place in the 2010 World Cup finals. The AIFF, in a meeting with the Asian Football Confederation bosses in New Delhi, has decided to form a Task Force by having four residential coaching camps in the four different zones  north, south, east and west. According to a source, the most talented under-15 boys from each zone will be chosen and will undergo training in residential camps. One coach will be in charge of each zonal camp with a senior coach in overall charge. A nationwide corporate meet has been proposed where top corporate houses will be invited. The houses can take the best national players on lien. Foreign players can also be hired.  Copyright 
